OL,6,FToday, it is understood that many of
OL,7,Fthem were suffering from - a condition
OL,8,Fthat was not recognised as a medical
OL,9,Fcondition until 1980.
OL,11,FIn 2006, 90 years after their deaths,
OL,12,Fthe soldiers were officially pardoned
OL,13,Fby the British Government.
OL,15,FDeliberately located at the most
OL,16,Feasterly part of the Arboretum where
OL,17,Fthe sun rises first, the memorial was
OL,18,Finstalled in 2001 and contains 309
OL,19,Fwooden stakes to represent each
OL,20,Fsoldier.
